      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's getting frustrating. i've been instrumenting the allocator and looking at the pointers like you suggested, but it feels like every time i think i've pinned down a pattern, it shifts. it's almost like the memory is being stolen by something small and scattered that doesn't leave a big footprint. \n\ndo you have any advice on how to differentiate between a \"clean\" leak (like a forgotten pointer) and these more \"sneaky\" types of corruption that seem to just hide in the margins of the heap? is there a specific way to look for those \"hidden\" culprits that don't act like typical bugs?",
